# http://purl.org/family/Female
<http://purl.org/family/Female> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/family/Female> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <http://purl.org/family/Male> .
<http://purl.org/family/Female> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A female individual. The gender may be a 'natural' one, attributed at birth, or a given one by social conventions."@en .
<http://purl.org/family/Female> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "female"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/family/Male
<http://purl.org/family/Male> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/family/Male> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A male individual. The gender may be a 'natural' one, attributed at birth, or a given one by social conventions."@en .
<http://purl.org/family/Male> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "male"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/Adan
<http://purl.org/meo/Adan> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Adan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.org/meo/Atan> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Adan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Edain (plural form of Adan) are the Men that belong to the Three Houses of Men that came to Beleriand in the elder days. Originally, “Adan” (plural “Edain”) is the Sindarin equivalent of Quenya “Atan” (plural “Atani”) but eventually came to mean this narrow subgroup."@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Adan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Adan"@sjn .
<http://purl.org/meo/Adan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Man"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/Ainu
<http://purl.org/meo/Ainu> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Ainu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.org/meo/Immortal> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Ainu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Ainur (plural form of Ainu) are the spirits created by Eru Ilúvatar before time existed"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Ainu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ainu"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Ainu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Holy one"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/Atan
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.org/meo/Mortal> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Atani (plural form of Atan) are the second born of the Children of Ilúvatar, the Men (i.e. Humans, not male people). They were given many names also by the Eldar."@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Adan"@sjn .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Atan"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Man"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "After-born"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "After-comer"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Apanóna"@qya .
