<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Follower"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Fírima"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Hildo"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Human"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Mortal"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Secondborn"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Atan> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Sickly"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/Casar
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.org/meo/Mortal> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Casari (plural form of Casar in Quenya), more often called with the Sindarin variant Naugrim (plural of Naug in Sindarin), are the Dwarves created by the Vala Aulë."@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Casar"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Dwarf"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Naug"@sjn .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Aulëonna"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Casar> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Child of Aulë"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/Elda
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass> <http://purl.org/meo/Quendë> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Eldar (plural form of Elda) are the Elves. They initially called themselves the Quendi, but the Vala Oromë, who met them at lake Cuiviénen under the stars, called them the Eldar. Now only the Quendi who followed Oromë to the West call themselves Eldar."@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Elda"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Eledh"@sjn .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Elf"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Firstborn"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "of the stars"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Elda> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "person of the stars"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin
<http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Eruhíni (plural form of Eruhin), literally “the Children of Eru”, are usually called the “Children of Ilúvatar”. They are the Elves and Men. “Children of Ilúvatar” is used to collectively refer to the two races of Men and Elves, and the singular form is rarely used."@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Child of Ilúvatar"@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Eruhin"@qya .
<http://purl.org/meo/Eruhin> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Child of Eru"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/EvilBeing
<http://purl.org/meo/EvilBeing> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/meo/EvilBeing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The evil beings are sentient agents that have chosen to do bad things, behave badly for the sake of doing bad, or became corrupted into doing evil. Some things are raised and bred to be evil. Some things are led to become evil by other evil beings by subversion. Some choose to become evil due to greed or as a way to overcome hardships of their lives."@en .
<http://purl.org/meo/EvilBeing> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "evil being"@en .
# 
# http://purl.org/meo/God
